   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1814-12_page01.jpg"/>
            <p>I am obliged by your mentioning your<lb/>
               little boys and rejoice to hear that they<lb/>
               are strong and healthy; but you do not tell<lb/>
               me how <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles's</persName> health goes on and<lb/>
               from a passage in his last I feel <choice>
                  <orig>apprehen<lb/>
               -sive</orig>
                  <reg>apprehensive</reg>
               </choice> that he is not quite as firm in health<lb/>
               as all his friends wish him to be.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               Pray set us at ease if you can upon<lb/>
               this subject my dear Madam<lb/>
               <unclear/>
               <lb/>
               Dec<unclear/> 1814<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               I wish you &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> the good old<lb/>
               fashioned compliments of the season<lb/>
               which will be <hi rend="underline">due</hi> before this comes<lb/>
               to your hands<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1814-12_page02.jpg"/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles</persName>
               <lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#St-Pauls-Churchyard_ENK">S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. Pauls <unclear>Church</unclear> Yard</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
         </div>
